					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Extiensive magician guide, somewhat material based.</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:amosblock@yahoo.com">Ryten</a> | 
		            8/17/2000 2:04:53 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">In my experience (which I admit is, perhaps, limited) Magicians are one of the easiest classes to play. Starting early with Summon food and Water at lvl 1, Magicians are blessed with myriad simple advantages. This is my guide on how best to capitalize on those advantages.<BR>
        First off, a brief note to any who plan to twink their Mage: if you are rich enough, equip them with a Shiny Mettalic Robe, a Sacrificial Dagger, and a Black Tome with Silvery Runes, also set aside a Gnoll Hide Tome, because at higher lvls a mage is better off unarmed. if you are only able to spend a couple of hundred plat, but wish to give the char a good start, I would recommend a Crude Stein, Dragoon Dirk (or if you are a small race a Dagger of Dropping), and a full Suit of Gossimer (Items suck as Golden Jaded Bracers/rings Blackened Iron Medallions etc. are also a good plan, but Full Suit Goss. is simplest)<BR>
        Now for the rest of us, the first step is to turn in your guild note, and destroy your PvP note ( you will not be needing to go Pvp for quite som time, and as a new one can be obtained by talking to a Priest of Discord at any time, you are best off with the room). Then Scribe and Memorize your spells, equip your Dagger and Tunic, and head out to the nearest newbie zone.   When in your early stages, remember to stay close to the guards, and if you get below 2 bubbles of health, run for cover. Also, although low lvl Summoning of food and water is an advantage, I would reccomend spending your money on other things until you reach lvl five, and stop getting water whyen you die, as until then you lose no EXP, just walk up to a guard and attack him, free food and water.<BR>
        Once you hit Lvl four, you are in a whole new world: Pets. In my opinion, the best pet to purchase is either Fire or Earth. The main Pros and cons of each are as follows:<BR>
                Fire:<BR>
                  + Hits hard and fast<BR>
                   - Dies easily, and is as likely to pull MOB to you as hold it off.<BR>
                Earth<BR>
                  + Roots with enough regularity to keep MOB off you, and has HIGH HP<BR>
                   - Ummm.... well.... In my opinion there aren;t any minuses ;)<BR>
        As you begin to have enough money to buy yourself items, work you way up through the ranks of armour. For a mage, the list is as follows: For everything but the robe, simply go from Cloth, to Raw Silk, to Gossimer. Cloth is easily available from merhcnats in the market (by the bank), and Raw Silk is purchaseable from players with the Tailoring Skill, for a MAXIMUM of 1pp per Ac, you should be able to get it for as little as half that. Gossimer is a different matter, and must be searched for, it is dropped by Hags in Unrest, which are approx lvl 30, so the price is substantial, but worth it to a mage since Ac is such a commodity, the only help I can give you is keep it on your WTB list.<BR>
        Robes, on the other hand are a much more complex list. First, when you have enough purchase the Violet Sr. Apprentice robe from your local magicians guild (I believe the color varies from town to town, Violet is in freeport) Next up from that is a Great Leap to a Flowing Black Robe, worth about 200-300pp, at Ac 8 Int 2. After that is a Green Silken Drape, the price of which fluxuates alot, but at this time is from 350-550pp GSD stats are Ac 8 Int 3 Dex 9 Sta 9 Sv Poison 15, and I am still using a GSD at lvl 19. After that is an Oracle robe, for 1kpp, but the improvement is arguable, and I personally am skipping the Oracle robe, and saving up for a Shiny Metallic Robes (SMR) which goes for around 10kpp.<BR>
        I apologize for the verbosity of this list, but I am trying to make sure all information is included, and hope to allow for twinks aswell as those with only normal capacity for money (for whom all this should be much later on)<BR>
        <BR>
<BR>
I will be adding a second edition to this later (as if anyone really cares ;) but as it is it is about 1:00, and I still have to get online for a few hours before bed (well not have too but... heck, theres a reasone Everquest is also known as Gamer's Crack ;)<BR>
<BR>
Well, please respond to this, and include anythink you would like to know in the next edition, and please criticise this part of the guide so I can improve.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
   - Ryten<BR>
     Magician, Lvl 19<BR>
     Order of the White Dragon<BR>
     Bristlebane
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
