			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				At level 4 I would stay away from using the fire pet. The damage shield is nice, but he just does not have the hit points you need. Water would be better til around 12.<BR>
At 8 take a water pet and go to town on the spiders in North Ro. It is fairly easy to take out red scarabs and dune spiders.<BR>
<BR>
Also, as you get into higher levels, the Air pet becomes king. It is a stunning monster and that saves your tanks and your clerics. <BR>
<BR>
Basically, you should get all 4 pets at every level because you have to prepare for any situation.<BR>
<BR>
Here was how I got to 44.<BR>
<BR>
1-4: Newbie zone.<BR>
4-8: Water pet at skeleton camp. (Nek or East Commons)<BR>
8-20: Water pet against spiders.<BR>
8-12 was dune spiders.<BR>
12-16 were carrion spiders.<BR>
16-20 were crag spiders.<BR>
Water pet is very resistant to poison so you'l only need him if you just want a diet of spiders.<BR>
20-24 Earth or Water on Garg Isle in OOT. You will have to tank as well, but its good exp.<BR>
24-29: Any pet at treants.<BR>
29-34: Fire or water against cyclopses and hill giants. (most likely you will have a druid snaring, so NO earth pet)<BR>
34-39: Air pet vs. Cynthia. She will get ripped apart by your little cloud as he stuns her and interrupts her.<BR>
39-44: Earth pet vs. Butcherblock dwarves. You need the earth pets hit points and ability to root. Trade off DD/heal/DD and the dwarf will be dead.<BR>
<BR>
any question send me a /t.<BR>
I play on E. Marr
				</font>
			</td>

